value.value: Chronic and progressive degeneration of the retina of the eye.
A disorder that is caused by pathologic changes in the spinal vasculature.
A finding that indicates the absence of an immune response to an antigen that is introduced to the skin.
Trauma resulting from illegal activity.
A concretion in the submandibular duct.
A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm affecting the lacrimal gland.
Trauma occurring within the confines of the home environment.
A finding that indicates the absence of an immune response to an antigen, which was introduced to the skin by the application of a patch containing the antigen.
Inflammation of the colon resulting from Clostridium Sordelli.
Candidiasis that is persistent or long-standing in nature.
A sensation of discomfort emanating from the inferiormost (verterbrochondral or vertebral) ribs.
A disorder of lipoprotein metabolism characterized by high levels of cholesterol and triglycerides in the blood. It is caused by elevation of low density and very low density lipoproteins.
Coughing up and spitting out of an overproduction of mucus in the respiratory tract in reaction to a constantly recurring irritant.

label.value: Femoral Hernia with Obstruction without Mention of Gangrene

value.value: The protrusion of contents of the abdominal cavity, into the femoral canal, which results in obstruction of intestinal peristalsis, with no mention of necrosis of the herniated contents.
A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm that affects the conjunctiva.

label.value: Umbilical Hernia with Obstruction without Mention of Gangrene

value.value: The protrusion of contents of the abdominal cavity through the abdominal wall, at the site of the umbilicus, which results in obstruction, without mention of necrosis of the herniated contents.

label.value: Hernia with Obstruction without Mention of Gangrene

value.value: The protrusion of an organ, or the fascia of an organ, through the wall of the cavity that normally contains it, which results in obstruction, without mention of necrosis of the herniated contents.

label.value: Ventral Hernia with Obstruction without Mention of Gangrene

value.value: The protrusion of contents of the abdominal cavity through the abdominal wall, at the site of the linea alba, which results in obstruction, without mention of necrosis of the herniated contents.
Destruction of tissue by a chemical substance.
A laboratory test result indicating an inheritable form of dysbetalipoproteinemia, in which there are excess intermediate-density lipoproteins in the blood.
Trauma to the pancreas.
Insomnia as a result of a physiological cause.
A malignant liver neoplasm that is not amenable to surgical resection.
A laboratory test result indicating abnormally high concentration of hydroxyproline in the urine.
A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm that affects the cornea.
An infectious process affecting the upper respiratory tract (nose, paranasal sinuses, pharynx, larynx, or trachea). Symptoms include congestion, sneezing, coughing, fever, and sore throat.
Pain experienced after a medical intervention through the time expected for associated acute effects to abate.

A non-congenital condition in which the head circumference is two standard deviations greater than the mean. Causes include infection, intraventricular hemorrhage, subdural hematoma, and arachnoid cysts.

An abnormal enlargement of the head, including the scalp, the cranial bone, and the contents of the cranium that is present at the time of birth; representative examples include tuberous sclerosis, neurofibromatosis, and various other genetic causes.
Accumulation of fluid in the peritoneal cavity resulting from the growth of primary or metastatic carcinoma in the peritoneum.
A laboratory test result indicating the results of the blood test are within normal parameters for the age and population.
Bleeding occurring after a medical intervention.
A laboratory test result indicating normal parameters after a phenolsulfonphthaliein test.
A non-neoplastic dental disorder that is present at birth.
Anemia due to a disorder that is persistent or long-standing in nature.
A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm that affects the choroid.
Gastroenteritis resulting from an infection with cytomegalovirus.
A cystic lesion in the chest wall.
Non-infectious pyrexia secondary to malignancy; it may be attributable to cytokines elaborated by neoplasms, and is a diagnosis of exclusion.

Acute compression of the thoracic cavity, causing  increased intrathoracic pressure and the backflow of blood from the right atrium and superior vena cava into the brachiocephalic and jugular veins, with resulting stagnation of blood flow and subsequent localized blood-oxygen desaturation in the head and neck.
A non-neoplastic disorder that is caused by pathologic changes in the ocular vasculature.
Neutropenia associated with fever, the latter indicating the presence of an infection.
An abscess that is located in the ureter.
A sensation of discomfort secondary to sampling of tissue or bodily fluid.
An early stage of diabetic retinopathy that is characterized by retinal hemorrhage and exudate, but without proliferation of the blood vessels.
Infection in the abdominal cavity resulting from injury, acute intestinal inflammation (e.g., acute appendicitis), intestinal perforation, or complication of abdominal surgery.
A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm affecting the lacrimal duct.
